=20
way of managing digital rights. Microsoft is making strenuous efforts in=20
this area but Sony with its interest in producing the video and music=20
people may be tempted to pirate is determined to establish itself as the=20
standard setter.
According to Sony, OpenMG X" consists of the following software modules:
1. An encoding module which adds digital rights management information,=20
such as the number of times content was copied or played, to music/movie=20
content and converts them into code at the distributors' end.
2. A server module which distributes digital rights management information=
=20
on content to the users' end.
3. A client module for developing application software compatible with=20
"OpenMG X"
Sony says that as "both a hardware manufacturer and content/service=20
